NUTRITION
A THEORETICAL MODEL FOR LINEARIZATION OF NUTRIENT RESPONSE
DATA. L. Preston Mercer*, Paul H. Morgan*, and N.W. Flodin.
Univ. of South Alabama, Mobile, AL 36688
The S-shaped curve is frequently encountered in the mea-
surement of nutritional responses. It is therefore desirable
to create a model which predicts the total curve (not just
the central "linear" portion) and its limits. The application
of saturation kinetics to nutrient response data provides such
a model and permits linearization of the data throughout all
or most of the observed response range. Sigmoidal saturation
PRESENTATION PREFERENCE
curves can be described by the Hill equation. A modification
of the Hill equation makes it applicable to nutritional data.
